<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="618" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Japan)/11–2045:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-21T13:00:00-05:00">November 21, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>2374. Final paragraph your 3903, Nov. 20. For your information
                                    and use in your discretion, Commanding General China Theater
                                    reported on 10 Nov that due to unsettled conditions in China it
                                    would not be possible to send Chinese occupational forces to
                                    Japan for several months and that “the Gimo<note n="34" xml:id="d618fn1">Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek.</note>
                                    regrets very much inability to participate and will do so should
                                    local situation clarify”.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>